The Honours Bachelor of Business Administration (Trades Management) degree program is a fully online degree-completion program delivered by Mohawk, Algonquin, and George Brown colleges. It builds on apprenticeship/journeyperson training or trade-related diploma programs.

The program prepares graduates for leadership roles in trades-related fields, such as business managers, project managers, quality control managers, maintenance and trades managers, and service-related managers. It also facilitates a pathway into graduate studies in business administration and management programs.

Students are required to complete a minimum of 420 hours (equivalent to 14 weeks) of paid co-op experience in a trades-related organization to enhance their professional development.

The program includes the following courses: 32 courses and 1 Integrated Experience are mandatory for degree completion. These include 24 mandatory courses and 8 Liberal Studies Electives of the student's choice.

Skills gained from this program include conducting research, using strategic planning techniques, developing marketing strategies, and applying financial information to strategic decision-making.

Graduates may choose self-employment as a small business owner or find leadership roles in various trades industries. Career options include: business managers, project managers, quality control managers, maintenance and trades managers, and service-related managers.

The text provides information on a flexible degree program offered by George Brown College, focusing on functional business units in the trades industry. Students are expected to conduct research, deploy strategic planning techniques, apply project and risk management principles, identify opportunities and challenges, and comply with relevant laws and regulations. Tuition varies based on chosen courses and does not include books or additional supplies. Financial assistance is available through OSAP for eligible applicants. Admission requirements include a post-secondary transcript and departmental review. The program is approved for a seven-year term starting from December 21, 2020, with possible renewal. Eligible professions in the trades industry include Construction Electrician, Electric Motor System Technician, Industrial Electrician, and Powerline Technician. Some college and university credits may qualify for exemptions. For more detailed information, applicants should contact the business department at business@georgebrown.ca or visit the transfer guide.

Admission requirements include a post-secondary transcript and departmental review. The program is approved for a seven-year term starting from December 21, 2020, with possible renewal. Eligible professions in the trades industry include Construction Electrician, Electric Motor System Technician, Industrial Electrician, and Powerline Technician. Some college and university credits may qualify for exemptions. For more detailed information, applicants should contact the business department at business@georgebrown.ca or visit the transfer guide.
